Communicated by:
Mary Marshall
<mjm2020@googlemail.com>

[China's most recent official reports to the OIE on new ASF outbreaks addressed outbreaks in domestic pigs in the provinces Shaanxi and Jiangsu. They were submitted on 13 and 17 Apr 2020, respectively, and are addressed in 20200424.7265246. Subscribers are referred to Mod.CRD's commentary in the said posting.

On 22 Apr 2020, the country reported ASF-positive pigs illegally moved from another province that were seized at a checkpoint at Qiaoheqiao Parking, Nanjiang, in Sichuan Province. The vehicle loaded 106 pigs, of which 2 were sick and died; the remaining 104 were destroyed.

According to information cited today (29 Apr 2020) from the official website of China's Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs, a video conference on the supervision and control of ASF was convened today. The meeting emphasized that animal husbandry and veterinary departments at all levels should insist on the recovery of hog production and the prevention and control of major animal diseases such as ASF, taking more pragmatic measures to ensure that the disease does not recur. The meeting pointed out that the current situation of prevention and control of ASF is still complex and grim, while the basis for the resumption of development of live pig production is not yet firm. Various prevention and control measures must be continuously strengthened. The risk of ASF spread is dependent upon prevention of illegal transfer of pigs; some breeding plants fail to fulfill their responsibilities. According to the report, prior to today's meeting, the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Affairs had dispatched 14 supervision teams to 54 cities and 27 counties in 27 provinces and autonomous regions to supervise ASF prevention and control and hog production, and inspected more than 200 sites on site (see the report, in Chinese, at https://tinyurl.com/y8ucgk82).

Another emerging animal epizootic that has recently obtained China's attention is African horse sickness (AHS), a vector-borne viral disease that has invaded Thailand. The Chinese authorities declared a state of alertness and is engaged in preparedness, having undertaken preventive measures (see commentary in 20200425.7265390). - Mod.AS

